3 Section 2. Section 13-1-107, MCA, is amended to read:
4 "13-1-107. Times Time for holding primary elections -- cost of municipal election. (1) On the first
5 Tuesday after the first Monday in June preceding a general election held in an even-numbered year, a primary
6 election must be held throughout the state.
7 (2) On the Tuesday following the second Monday in September preceding a general election held
8 in an odd-numbered year, a primary election, if required, must be held throughout the state.
9 (3)(2) The cost of a municipal election must be paid by the municipality."
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Transition. (1) For a municipal officer whose term of office ends in
12 January 2026, there must be an election in 2025 for a one-year term of office.
13 (2) For a municipal officer whose term of office ends in January 2028 or January 2030, there must
14 be a special election for a one-year term proceeding when their term of office is set to end. This special election
15 must take place during the preceding even-numbered year general election.
16
17 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Saving clause. [This act] does not affect rights and duties that matured,
18 penalties that were incurred, or proceedings that were begun before [the effective date of this act].
19
20 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Effective date. [This act] is effective on passage and approval.
21
22 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Applicability. [This act] applies to all municipal elections scheduled on
23 or after [the effective date of this act].
24 - END -
